S T A T E O F R H O D E I S L A N D
IN GENERAL ASSEMBLY
JANUARY SESSION, A.D. 2025
____________
S E N A T E R E S O L U T I O N
HONORING AND THANKING THE HONORABLE MARTHA BALL FOR HER 50 YEARS
OF SERVICE TO THE TOWN OF NEW SHOREHAM
Introduced By: Senators DiMario, Sosnowski, Ciccone, Britto, LaMountain, Thompson,
Lauria, Felag, Appollonio, and Mack
Date Introduced: January 21, 2025
Referred To: Recommended for Immediate Consideration
1 WHEREAS, Martha Ball has been involved in the governance of the Town of New
2 Shoreham for over 50 years, covering a broad range of roles starting in the early 1980s; and
3 WHEREAS, Councilwoman Ball served on the Town Council for 21 years in total during
4 two major periods from 1991 to 2004 and 2016 to 2024, and as First Warden from 2001 to 2004;
5 and
6 WHEREAS, She started her public service career in the Finance Department in 1978 and
7 served as Town Treasurer from 1981 to 1990; and
8 WHEREAS, Martha Ball also served on the Zoning Board from 1980 to 1992 and was
9 Chair until 1991; and
10 WHEREAS, She also was the clerk and deeply engaged in the sewer plant construction
11 and operations from 1976 to 2000; and
12 WHEREAS, Her public service also extends to numerous other positions including her
13 service on the Historic District Commission; the Conservation Committee; the Hodge Acquisition
14 Team; Island Light & Power; the Tourism Council; the Washington County Regional Planning
15 Council; the Water District; the Ball O’Brien Planning & Management Committee; the 250th
16 Anniversary Committee; the Commission on Motor Vehicles for Hire; the Density Discussion
17 Panel; the Fire/Police Station Trustees; the Housing Board; the Planning Board as a Town
18 Council Representative; and as an Assistant Moderator; and
19 WHEREAS, Martha’s contribution has not only been her prodigious body of work, but

1 also her counsel and her knowledge of Island history has been and remains irreplaceable, and she
2 will surely be called upon by future Town Councils for her extraordinary breadth of experience
3 and recollection, now, therefore be it
4 RESOLVED, That this Senate of the State of Rhode Island hereby sincerely thanks
5 Martha Ball for her long-term participation, perspective and true commitment to the well-being of
6 Block Island and the Town of New Shoreham; and be it further
7 RESOLVED, That the Secretary of State be and hereby is authorized and directed to
8 transmit a duly certified copy of this resolution to the Honorable Martha Ball.
